WEBVTT

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:05.120
This video will walk through the process of setting up a SageMaker domain with access to

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:10.480
RStudio Workbench. So the first thing we need to do is make sure that we have access to an RStudio

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:16.959
license within the AWS License Manager. So navigate to that within the AWS console. There's two ways

00:00:16.959 --> 00:00:21.920
that you can have access to a license here. One is either by purchasing an RStudio Workbench

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:26.879
license from the Amazon Marketplace. The other is by reaching out directly to RStudio and requesting

00:00:26.879 --> 00:00:30.879
a license to be granted into your account. In the case that a license has been granted,

00:00:30.879 --> 00:00:34.560
you would need to then accept that license. So that's something that needs to be done with the

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:40.080
License Manager. In here, I can see that I have an RStudio Workbench SageMaker license that's

00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:43.919
available. This is one that's been granted. I also have one that came from the Marketplace

00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:49.439
available in this account as well. So as long as you have a license available for RStudio Workbench,

00:00:49.439 --> 00:00:53.919
either one that's been granted to you by RStudio or one that you've purchased through the Marketplace,

00:00:53.919 --> 00:00:56.480
you can then go through the setup process within SageMaker.

00:00:57.680 --> 00:01:01.840
After I've confirmed that I have a license that's ready to go in License Manager, I'll navigate to

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:07.680
the SageMaker landing page. Here, I can just click on Get Started. And this will bring me to this

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:11.839
place where I can configure my SageMaker domain. I'm going to go ahead and set that up. I'm going

00:01:11.839 --> 00:01:17.680
to choose Standard Setup here because I want to adjust a few things specifically related to the

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:22.480
RStudio Workbench setup. Here, I can choose which authentication mechanism I want to use,

00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:29.519
set up a default execution role. There's one that can be created for you if you need to create

00:01:29.519 --> 00:01:37.120
an execution role in here. One thing that's worth noting is in order for you to have access to

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:43.839
the license that you have inside of AWS License Manager, you'll need to make sure that this

00:01:43.839 --> 00:01:48.959
particular execution role has License Manager permissions. There's some documentation and

00:01:48.959 --> 00:01:53.839
details about that in a blog post by Amazon. But essentially, you just need to make sure that this

00:01:53.839 --> 00:01:58.959
execution role has permission to read License Manager information so that it can pull the

00:01:58.959 --> 00:02:06.720
license that you have for RStudio. Next, we can choose a VPC, subnets, all the relevant different

00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:13.919
pieces of information that we might want to set up here. This is where we set up SageMaker Studio.

00:02:13.919 --> 00:02:17.440
I'm not going to dive too deeply into this. If you're using SageMaker Studio,

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:20.720
you have some options here about how that's set up and configured. I'm just going to leave

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:25.199
all the defaults in place. And then the third step here are the RStudio settings. So you'll

00:02:25.199 --> 00:02:29.919
see that it will automatically identify that you have a Workbench license detected. And so it will

00:02:29.919 --> 00:02:35.679
enable these options within your SageMaker domain. This first option here is what instance type I

00:02:35.679 --> 00:02:42.320
want to run for the persistent RStudio Workbench environment. A T3 medium is typically sufficient.

00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:47.119
This instance runs 24-7. But if you choose a T3 medium, which is the default,

00:02:47.119 --> 00:02:52.000
you don't pay for that instance. It's an instance that is just provided for you by Amazon as part

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:58.479
of your SageMaker environment. Then I need to choose an execution role for my RStudio server.

00:02:59.199 --> 00:03:02.399
In this case, there's this RStudio execution role that I've previously created.

00:03:03.279 --> 00:03:08.399
If I want to pre-configure RStudio Connect and RStudio Package Manager URLs, I can put those

00:03:08.399 --> 00:03:15.759
in here. These become the default publication endpoints and default package repository within

00:03:15.759 --> 00:03:20.000
Workbench once you've set that up. Once I've gone through all these options, I can hit Submit.

00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:25.520
And then my domain will be created. This takes a few minutes for the domain to get up and running.

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:30.880
Once the domain is running, the next step that I need to go through is add individual users onto

00:03:30.880 --> 00:03:35.759
the domain, which you can see here in the Users panel. When I click on Add User, it'll bring up

00:03:35.759 --> 00:03:42.399
a menu. And one of the things that I can do when I add a user is determine what their status is as

00:03:42.399 --> 00:03:47.279
an RStudio Workbench user, whether they are unauthorized, a standard user, or an admin user.

00:03:47.839 --> 00:03:53.119
And if I add them as either a standard or admin user, it gives them access to access RStudio

00:03:53.119 --> 00:03:59.839
Workbench. Now that the domain is ready, we can go ahead and go through this add user process.

00:04:00.479 --> 00:04:06.080
Come in here, choose some sort of name. I'll just choose my own name. Define an execution role.

00:04:07.039 --> 00:04:10.880
And then here, again, these are settings related specifically to SageMaker Studio, which you can

00:04:10.880 --> 00:04:15.360
adjust if you want to. And then finally, here's where I can choose how I set this user up for

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:19.359
RStudio, specifically whether they're an unauthorized user, which prevents them from

00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:24.079
accessing RStudio, an RStudio user, which gives them standard access, and an RStudio admin,

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:27.200
which will provide access to the admin dashboard within RStudio.

00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:32.480
Once this user gets provisioned, I can use the drop-down menu over here on the right-hand side

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:38.880
to launch either Studio, if I've given them access to that, or RStudio, as I've given this user

00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:44.000
access to. Again, it'll take a moment for the user profile to be created. Once that's done,

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:49.200
I can select something like RStudio, and I'll get dropped into an RStudio session on SageMaker,

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:54.799
and I'm ready to go. In this particular case, we added this user to the admin group. So,

00:04:54.799 --> 00:05:00.399
if I wanted to, I could come in and adjust the URL and add admin at the end of it to gain access to

00:05:00.399 --> 00:05:04.559
the admin dashboard for that user as well. Hopefully, this helps get an idea of what

00:05:04.559 --> 00:05:09.519
it takes to set up a SageMaker domain with access to RStudio. Thanks for watching.

